The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A man died and another was injured in two mishaps in the city since Thursday night. Laksman Rikiason, 52, was knocked down by an unidentified vehicle on the EM Bypass, near Tata gate, around 5.30am on Friday. He was taken to NRS hospital, where he succumbed to his injuries. Around 11.25pm on Thursday, an unidentified vehicle hit Hari Charan Sahani, 45, on Strand Road. He was taken to SSKM Hospital. Both the drivers fled.				   Traffic disruption: Political demonstrations disrupted traffic across the city on Friday. About 15,000 SUCI supporters took part in a rally from Hedua to Metro channel to protest price rise. The rally started around 1.30pm and reached Esplanade around 5pm.																																																								  About 200 Congress supporters, led by Deepa Das Munshi, formed a human chain and burnt the effigy of Bal Thackeray, to protest his comments on Rahul Gandhi at Hazra around 1.30pm. Congress supporters also held another demonstration on the same issue at the MG Road-CR Avenue crossing.   Help arrested: Rekha Haldar was arrested late on Thursday for being allegedly involved in a theft at her employers house in Salt Lakes AB block. She was produced in the court of additional chief judicial magistrate of Bidhannagar on Friday and remanded in police custody for three days. A sweater and Rs 10,000 were stolen from the house.				   Rail route: The route of the Howrah-Agra Cantonment Chambal Express has been extended till Mathura. Trains leaving Howrah will run till Mathura from February 12. The first train from Mathura to Howrah will leave on February 8. The train will start from Howrah at 5.45pm on Fridays and from Mathura at 4.20am on Mondays.                                                                                                                                               
